{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "During Covid-19 pandemic, make PPE on prescription for those most at risk.",
        "additional_details": "Since the start of the Covid-19 pandemic all Personal Protection Equipment (PPE) has become in short supply and prices have been gauged. PPE is vital for those most vulnerable from this infection so that they can continue receiving the care and protection they need. GPs across UK should prioritise these groups and start issuing PPE on prescription.",
        "background": "PPE (personal protection equipment) like hand sanitiser, gloves and face masks should be prioritised for those in the at risk category, the more vulnerable,and anyone with a serious long term condition of the lung & heart, severe asthma, lowered immunity and cancer.",
